  "aboutOrderExpirationExplanation": "The timeout in seconds after which a trade waiting for action (e.g. invoice or payment) is automatically canceled.",
  "aboutHoldInvoiceExpExplanation": "The time window in seconds during which the Lightning hold invoice must be settled.",
  "aboutHoldInvoiceCltvExplanation": "The CLTV delta (block count) used for hold invoices, controlling how long the HTLC can remain locked.",
  "aboutInvoiceExpWindowExplanation": "The time window in seconds within which the buyer must submit a Lightning invoice after the trade is initiated.",
  "aboutProofOfWorkExplanation": "The minimum proof-of-work difficulty required for Nostr events on this instance. 0 means no PoW is required.",
  "aboutMaxOrdersPerResponseExplanation": "The maximum number of orders returned in a single relay response. Limits bandwidth usage.",
